members.title: Lyellian Principle
members.text: For two strata A and B it holds: (i) The more A and B are similar in their FSAs, the more they are similar in age, (ii) the more A and B are similar in age, the more they are similar in their FSAs and (iii) if A and B are sufficiently unsimilar in age, then they have no species in common #dat-met
